      "description": "Available is a mechanically sound 1999 Porsche 911 Carrera 2, featuring the desirable 3.4L M96 flat-six and a 6-speed G96 manual transaxle. This example has been fastidiously maintained with a focus on preventative engineering; the IMS bearing has been upgraded to a ceramic dual-row solution, and the rear main seal (RMS) was replaced during the last clutch service. The naturally aspirated powerplant retains excellent compression and exhibits no bore scoring symptoms. Handling is sharp thanks to a refreshed multi-link rear suspension and Bilstein B6 dampers, while the four-piston Brembo monoblock calipers provide firm, consistent pedal feel. The chassis remains rigid and true, though the finish shows minor road rash commensurate with its status as a high-performance driver\u2019s car. A recent DME report confirms no over-revs in ranges 2 through 6.",
